All the Performance parameters BTE, BSFC were calculated based on the acquired data. Emission parameters including CO, NOx, HC, and smoke were analyzed to assess the ecological effect of the ULDP20GQD blends compared to ULDP20 and standard diesel fuel. The experimental results were systematically compared to understand the effects of GQD additives on combustion characteristics and emissions profiles. the experimental setup and procedure were designed to provide detailed insights into the feasibility and performance enhancements offered by GQD additives in ULDP20 blends as an alternative fuel source for DI diesel engines. The systematic approach ensured rigorous testing under controlled conditions, facilitating accurate evaluation and comparison with conventional fuels (Table 2
                        , Fig. 1
                        ).
